## Step 1:  Recall the definition of the binomial coefficient
$\dbinom{n}{r} = \dfrac{n!}{r!(n-r)!}$
## Step 2:  Plug in the given values for $n$ and $r$ into the definition of the binomial coefficient
$\dbinom{85}{82} = \dfrac{85!}{82!(85-82)!}$
## Step 3:  Simplify the expression using the properties of factorials
$\dbinom{85}{82} = \dfrac{85!}{82!3!}$
## Step 4:  Cancel out the common factors in the numerator and denominator
$\dbinom{85}{82} = \dfrac{85 \times 84 \times 83}{3 \times 2 \times 1}$
## Step 5: Evaluate the expression to find the final value of the binomial coefficient
$\dbinom{85}{82} = \dfrac{85 \times 84 \times 83}{3 \times 2 \times 1} = \dfrac{50751060}{6}$
